<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-02-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-02-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="1063" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1063">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">Julian Pauncefote</persName>
                                to Mr. <persName type="to">Sherman</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-02-21"><hi rend="italic">February 21,
                                    1898</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: At the request of Sir Alfred Maloney,
                            governor of the Windward Islands, I have the honor to convey the
                            heartfelt sympathy of that colony with the Government and people of the
                            United States in the loss sustained through the explosion on board the
                                <hi rend="italic">Maine</hi>.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Julian Pauncefote.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>